communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All current "Brady lists" and "Giglio lists" (per Brady v. Maryland/Giglio v. United States) maintained by your office, along with accompanying potential impeachment material.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Composite Sketch Released June 15, 2016
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any information on the previously unreleased composite sketch jointly released by the Sacramento County Sheriff's Department and the FBI at a press conference on June 15, 2016. Specifically, I would like to know which case the composite sketch came from. There were 3 composite sketches released to the public at the press conference. The first one came from the 2/2/1978 Maggiore homicide and was released to the public on April 16, 1978. The second one came from the Rod Miller shooting and had been released sometime after 2001.  The third one had been previously unreleased and I would like to know which case the composite sketch came from.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Neville

All Memphis Animal Services controlled medicine records for 12/3/25 through 12/10/25. The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Cindy Marx

communications.subject: Re: Tennessee Public Records Act Request: Tennessee State - Under Armour
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:


Thank you for reaching out.


To help avoid any confusion or the possibility of missing something you've requested, I recommend completing our Tennessee Public Records Request form. This system is in place to track requests and ensure that we’re able to provide the information you need in a timely and efficient manner.


You can find the form on our website by selecting the "Records Request Form" at the following link:
https://www.tnstate.edu/legal/public-records-requests.aspx.


Include the Power of Attorney Document as well.


Filling out the form helps ensure your request is clearly documented and processed as smoothly as possible.


Please let me know if you have any questions.


Best,



Public Records Request
Office of the General Counsel
Tennessee State University
3500 John A. Merritt Boulevard
Nashville, TN 37209-1561
p: (615) 963-7923
https://www.tnstate.edu/legal/public-records-requests.aspx
